JB
4.0 out of 5 starsGreat Concept, Not Perfect
March 14, 2019
Verified Purchase
First the good:
- Really cool concept
- Looks good - I got the gray one which is gray with the slightest brown tint.
- Fit and finish is pretty good
- The mattress that comes with it is decent - nice and soft

Next, unfortunately, the not as good. When reading the following comments please keep in mind that nothing has broken on mine (although it hasn't been slept on by two adults yet) and I don't have any proof for what I say.
- I should have considered this more before purchasing, but I have some serious doubts that this thing will hold 2 regular 'modern' adults without starting to seriously bow in the center (making a very uncomfortable bed for 2 people) or even cracking. Keep in mind that a bed is often sat on at an edge or at the foot of the bed. That is a point load and the bed has to be able to handle. Since returning this is out of the question I am using metal L brackets to beef it up and will be building wooden center supports to make this thing stronger. Those supports will just have to be stored in my garage when not using in bed form.
- The mattress while comfortable may be a little too thin again for 'modern' adults. I will be bolstering with another mattress underneath to provide additional thickness.

I'm not giving this a bad rating because it is nicely built, looks good, and may work fine if you will be using for kids or pretty light adults. But if your guests are like most adults today then you might think a little harder if this will work for you. Personally, I kind of wish I hadn't purchased.
